Job Description 2 :

What you will do:
You will act as a Business Analyst staffed on projects for various clients. You will learn the management consulting job and grow into a consultant role. You will handle business analysis, market research, and client presentations. You are expected to work collaboratively in a team environment with people at all levels within an organization.

Key Attributes:
Strong analytical and quantitative problem-solving skills with great attention to detail.
Demonstrable ability to perform in a high-pressure situation.
Entrepreneurial and innovation-driven mindset.

Skills:
Problem Structuring, Quantitative Assumption Validation, Market Sizing Awareness, Structured Documentation, Executive Presentations, Hypothesis Prioritization, Client-Ready Deliverables.

